The paper discusses attacking machine learning models in the context of network security, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a cyber kill chain, which is a concept commonly used in the field of security informatics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes more secure processes for machine learning-based security solutions, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
